albums.title: Unleashed
albums.description: A bold sonic release of emotion and unrest. This album explores the tension between control and chaos, combining raw energy with untamed rhythm.

albums.title: Ghosts
albums.description: An emotional journey through presence and absence. This album captures the lingering weight of memory, the ache of uncertainty, and the echo of what almost was.

albums.title: Sinner's Feast
albums.description: A distorted feast of power and temptation. With heavy undertones and fierce textures, this collection leans into raw instinct, grit, and catharsis.

albums.title: Greatest Hits
albums.description: A collection of raw ideas, experiments, and early statements. These tracks reflect the messy beginnings of a voice still forming—and growing stronger.

albums.title: Awakenings
albums.description: A reflection of personal emergence. These tracks explore moments of clarity, rebuilding, and the quiet strength it takes to become whole again.

albums.title: UNMUTE
albums.description: A call to power and presence. This album breaks through silence with conviction—an anthem for reclaiming voice, body, and life without apology.

albums.title: Exit Wounds
albums.description: Wounds don’t mean weakness—they mean you made it out. EXIT WOUNDS is a gritty post-recovery statement, capturing the truth of survival without pretending it’s neat.

albums.title: Afterlight
albums.description: Life after the wreckage. AFTERLIGHT imagines a world rebuilt—where peace is messy, love is steady, and the future is finally in motion.

tracks.title: Afterlight
tracks.description: Hints of what came before, but focused on what’s ahead. Not a happy ending — a better beginning.

tracks.title: Real Ones Stay
tracks.description: Loyalty is louder than words — she finally sees that. Not promises — presence.

tracks.title: Gas in the Tank
tracks.description: Still tired, still bruised, but the engine’s running. No time to stop — there’s too much life left to live.

tracks.title: Skyline Kids
tracks.description: Eyes to the future, pride, quiet fears, strong hopes. They’ll go farther than we did — that’s the point.

tracks.title: No Blueprint
tracks.description: There’s no map for what comes next — we build it anyway. The future’s DIY — and that’s beautiful.

tracks.title: Messy Forever
tracks.description: Every fight, every laugh, every weird Tuesday — it’s ours. Love doesn’t look clean — it looks lived-in.

tracks.title: Open Door Days
tracks.description: Breakfast smells, loud music, open hearts. Peace isn’t silence — it’s freedom to be loud together.

tracks.title: Barefoot Proof
tracks.description: No heels, no mask — she walks her own earth. Sometimes healing looks like dancing barefoot.

tracks.title: Blood & Hope
tracks.description: The things we pass down, the ones we end. This is how you change a legacy.

tracks.title: Midnight Groceries
tracks.description: Late runs for milk, inside jokes, background peace. It’s not the milestones — it’s the mundane magic.

tracks.title: Firewatcher
tracks.description: Love as observation, not ownership. I’m not here to fix her — just to witness her shine.

tracks.title: Roots Before Rockets
tracks.description: You don’t fly until your feet know the ground. Make home strong. Then launch.

tracks.title: See It Through
tracks.description: It’s not about starting over — it’s about finishing strong. This time, no one's backing out. We see it through.

albums.title: Walk Good, Rastaman
albums.description: A spiritual journey through Rastafari life: roots, faith, unity, herb, and the soulful rhythms of Jamaica.

albums.title: Nine Lives, Two Souls
albums.description: The ultimate cat concept album exploring feline duality through the cats' own voices. From angelic purrs to chaotic zoomies, experience life through whiskers and claws.

albums.title: Forge of Fire
albums.description: The legendary saga of Brokkr, master craftsman of the Nine Realms. From his trials in Muspelheim to his rise as founder of the Forge Council, these songs chronicle hope, brotherhood, and the eternal flame of creation.

albums.title: Magic & Wonder
albums.description: A delightful collection of imaginative songs for children and families. From adventure tales to gentle lullabies, these songs spark creativity and wonder while providing music that parents won't mind hearing on repeat during car rides, story time, and quiet moments.

albums.title: Time Capsule
albums.description: Step into a musical time machine! 'Time Capsule' whisks you through a century of catchy tunes, as each song celebrates the sound and spirit of a different decade. From jazz age jams to disco fever, grunge rebellion, and beyond, this album is a vibrant, nostalgic celebration of how music timelessly captures our collective story.

albums.title: Daily Grace Collection
albums.description: A collection of peaceful worship songs with vocals, perfect for prayer and meditation

albums.title: I Hate Music
albums.description: Ever wanted to turn down the volume on the world? "I Hate Music" is the ultimate anti-anthem for everyone who's ever left the dance floor early or found beauty in silence. Packed with tongue-in-cheek hooks, ironic singalongs, and stubborn declarations of independence, this album takes all the things that make music irresistible... and dares to look away.

albums.title: Polka, Please
albums.description: A wild invitation to the dancefloor, 'Polka, Please' brings together old-world oomph, hip-hop flair, and unpredictable joy. This one-track wonder throws tradition a colorful party hat, boasting madcap energy and irresistible rhythm.

albums.title: Steel On Asphalt
albums.description: An unfiltered tribute to the long-haul life: grit, pride, fatigue, and the wild poetry of the open road. These tracks pull no punches and salute every mile earned.
